      <refsection>
        <title>Keplerian State</title>

        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term><literal>SMA</literal></term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The SMA field is the spacecraft orbit's osculating
              Keplerian semimajor axis in the coordinate system chosen in the
              Spacecraft Coordinate System field. SMA must be strictly greater
              than 1 m or less than -1 m to avoid numerical issues in the
              conversions to other state types. For circular and elliptical
              orbits ( 0 &lt;= ECC &lt; 0.9999999 ) SMA should only be greater
              than 1 m and for hyperbolic orbits (ECC &gt; 1.0000001) SMA
              should be less than -1 m. GMAT does not support the creation of
              parabolic orbits.</para>

              <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Type</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>numeric</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Default</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Limits</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <informalequation>
                      <alt>\left| SMA \right| &gt; 10^{-3}</alt>

                      <mathphrase>|SMA| &gt; 1 m</mathphrase>
                    </informalequation>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Units</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>km</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
              </variablelist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><literal>ECC</literal></term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The ECC field is the spacecraft orbit's osculating
              eccentricity. For circular or elliptic orbits, ECC must be
              greater than or equal to 0.0, and less than or equal to
              0.9999999 to avoid numerical issues in the conversion to other
              state types as the Keplerian elements are undefined for
              parabolic orbits. For hyperbolic orbits ECC must be greater than
              or equal to 1.0000001. See also the SMA description. </para>

              <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Type</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>numeric</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Default</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Limits</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Units</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>none</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
              </variablelist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><literal>INC</literal></term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The INC field is the spacecraft orbit's osculating
              inclination, in degrees, with respect to the selected coordinate
              system. </para>

              <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Type</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>numeric</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Default</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Limits</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Units</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>degrees</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
              </variablelist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><literal>RAAN</literal></term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The RAAN field is the spacecraft orbit's osculating right
              ascension of the ascending node, in degrees, with respect to the
              selected coordinate system. </para>

              <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Type</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>numeric</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Default</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Limits</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Units</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>degrees</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
              </variablelist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><literal>AOP</literal></term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The AOP field is the spacecraft orbit's osculating
              argument of periapsis, in degrees, with respect to the selected
              coordinate system. </para>

              <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Type</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>numeric</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Default</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Limits</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Units</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>degrees</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
              </variablelist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>

          <varlistentry>
            <term><literal>TA</literal></term>

            <listitem>
              <para>The TA field is the spacecraft orbit's osculating true
              anomaly. </para>

              <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Type</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para>numeric</para>
                  </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                  <term>Default</term>

                  <listitem>
                    <para></para>
